features: Toddler Pacifier - Natursutten's Large Size natural rubber pacifiers are the perfect size for older babies and toddlers 12 months of age and up. We also offer Small Size pacis for 0-6 months and Medium Size pacifiers for 6-12 months. Need Pacifier Storage? Add our PaciPouch Pacifier Holder, 100% Organic Cotton and machine washable

Safer and Softer - Our pacifiers are made exclusively from pure natural rubber from Hevea Brasiliensis trees. They are free of BPA, phthalates, and chemical softening agents. Each natural rubber pacifier is naturally softer than silicone pacifiers and gentle on sensitive gums

Best Pacifier for Breastfed Babies - Ultimately, the best pacifier is the one your baby will take. We've found that better breastfeeding pacifiers feature a Round shield that gently rests upon baby's nose, which simulates breastfeeding. Similarly, a Round bulb nipple more closely mimics the natural breast, which reduces nipple confusion in breastfed babies

Supporting Healthy Teeth and Breathing - Your baby may instead prefer a butterfly pacifier shield that leaves a cut-out to let their nose be free to wriggle around and breathe! They might also prefer an Orthodontic pacifier nipple, which is flat on the bottom and reduces stress on baby's bottom teeth and jaw

One Piece Baby Pacifiers - Whichever binkie is right for your baby, all Natursutten pacifiers feature one-piece construction with no joints or cracks where dirt and other yucks can collect. They're also super easy to clean with mild soap and running water. Pediatricians recommend replacing a well-used or worn pacifier every 4-6 weeks.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: The 100% natural rubber line of pacifiers made in Italy. Natursutten pacifiers are made with all-natural rubber, with no BPA, phthalates, or chemical softening agents. The patented, one-piece design is free of joints or cracks where dirt can accumulate, and the pacifiers are easier to clean. Crafted in Italy by a family-run business, each Natursutten pacifier takes 7 weeks and 20 hand-held steps to go from liquid sap to finished product. Since the rubber from the Hevea Brasiliensis tree is softer than the silicone in mass-produced pacifiers, your baby will enjoy a gentler, more natural feel.

PACIFIERS SAFER BY DESIGN The first thing you’ll notice is the single-piece design. This means no joints or cracks where yucky things can hide, and it’s easy to wash by hand with just mild soap and warm water. Natursutten’s construction adheres to the strictest European and U.S. safety standards. Babies love our Natursutten pacifiers. One reason may be the soft rubber, which has a more natural feel than the artificial silicone used in mass- produced pacifiers. You’ll understand at first touch. NATURAL RUBBER Made from liquid rubber milk from sustainably harvested rubber trees.Natural rubber is softer than siliconeCrafted in Italy by a family-run business, each Natursutten pacifier takes 7 weeks and 20 hand-held steps to go from liquid sap to finished product.Natural rubber has no BPA, phthalates, or chemical softening agents. WHICH MODEL DO I CHOOSE? PaciPixy and PaciPouch contain no clips, buttons or other potential choking hazards - Keeping it a safe and soft addition; easy to hold on to and easy to find.

When you buy a Natursutten pacifier, you and your baby avoid Allergy-causing substancesArtificial colorsChemical softenersParabens, PVC, and phthalates Each pacifier is made from 100% natural rubber, simply better for your baby.

Original - round Original - orthodontic Butterfly - round Butterfly - orthodontic PaciPouch Breastfeeding Baby Preferred ✓ ✓ ✓ Eases Stress on New Teeth ✓ ✓ Extra-Comfy Nose Notch ✓ ✓ Ventilated for Easy Breathing ✓ ✓ ✓ ✓

ALL NATURAL Our commitment to a better Earth doesn’t end with the all-natural rubber in our pacifiers. Our packaging is printed with natural soy ink. Even the clear window is made of bio plastic—from corn, not petroleum.

The Natursutten Story Anne-Dorthe Schroeder started Natursutten (which means 'natural pacifier' in Danish) in 2006 when she couldn’t find a healthy option for her newborn son. “The media is full of stories about dangerous baby gear, recalls, and harmful plastics. As a new mother, I thought about how many hours my son was going to have a pacifier in his mouth, and I was determined to find a truly safe alternative. I felt I owed it to my child and other babies around the world – to do better.”

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 25, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars We are in love with these! Perfect pacifiers but they will bounce so keep your eyes peeled for them!
reviews.reviewText: These are such perfect pacifiers! My son loves them and I am happy with the quality/natural ingredients as well. We only use two pacifier brands, this and Chicco. I am a little nervous about any that are not a complete, 1 piece due to some recalls of the two parts coming undone and the child swallowing. I know its rare but just puts my mind at east having 1 solid piece.My favorite thing about them is that there is a gap between the bulb portion and the back of the pacifier (shown in pic) This seems like it is more comfortable to me, it leaves a space for his teeth and lips. Other pacifiers seem to have a smaller space and doesn't leave room for the lips to rest. If that makes any sense the way I explained it. The rubber is very soft and pliable which also seems more comfy. The only complaints that I would have, which are so incredibly minor, is that they don't come with a case or cover. I really think thats important since they get shoved into diaper bags or around the house. I mean ya you can just rinse them or use pacifier wipes (or the default mommy's mouth) when you are out and about, I still prefer a case and its always nice when you don't have to buy one. Sooo we do have allot of the Chicco pacifier that we love also. They come with a huge case that I am the most gigantic fan of. Since they are so soft and pliable I can squeeze 3 of these babies into one of the Chicco cases! Due to the rubber they bounce and therefore easily misplaced. For this reason and due to them being a little more spendy than other brands, we only use them at home since I will eventually find them lol. Outside, they drop or he throws it, bounce bounce far away and who knows where they end up! We use the Chicco for when we are out and about. I really can't complain about the price because I think they are worth it. I also accidentally ordered the bulb shape, the chiccos are the angled shape. So I was worried that he wouldn't take to them but he actually loves it! Then, due to the bouncing and having lost a couple, I started using the Chicco while being out and thought he wouldn't like the two different shapes. It hasn't effected him at all he really likes both. Oh and he loves to chew on these also, not sure if he likes the texture or the squeaky sound of the rubber lol. I think I covered all the details so hope this review helps! Overall I definitely love them and would suggest! Oh one more thing! I recall reading a couple negative reviews about two things: The discoloration when you sanitize. yes, it turns a cloudy color but goes back to normal once it cools and dries. The other thing was the little indentation for their nose. Someone had said its really not that big of an indentation and not much of a difference if you order these or the round shape. I think I would agree with that. Im not sure if there is a price difference but if so and the round shape without the indentation is cheaper then I would just go with that. Since the bulb shape is consistent all around, my son constantly turns it upside down so that the nose indentation is on the bottom and it doesn't make any difference, it still doesn't hit his nose.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 22, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars To all those on the fence after reading the "negatives"
reviews.reviewText: I can't say enough amazing things about these binks. Curious what someone could possibly say negative about these (short of your baby simply not liking it), I read through the negatives. Let's start by saying the pacifier is natural rubber. My son is over two now, still fully bink-dependent, and I've gone through probably 40. I have never once noticed a smell. They clearly state that you must boil the pacifier prior to use, and that by doing so, the material will turn whitish. It also tells you if you wait, it will turn back to its original state. They also tell you the pacifier will become sticky and breakdown, and that they recommend replacing it every 4-6 weeks. If you're baby/toddler is teething or is a binky chewer, this can easily accelerate the breakdown. I've never once seen any of our pacifiers "crack". I'm assuming these reviews are referring to some sort of material breakdown at the base, where saliva accumulates the most, especially the ones that reference it happening "after only a month", as that's into the replacement time frame. Natural rubber pacifiers are not synthetic cancer pops. They breakdown. They become tacky. They turn whitish at the base eventually. They require replacement. But you know what they don't do? They don't fill your baby with toxins. Them's the breaks, kids. These aren't reasons to return your pacifier. As Tommy Boy says, "it's on the box". Read that box first before you toss it in and trash, and of course - weigh your options. There are a lot of amazing natural pacifiers, I'm just baby-lead to Natursutten by his preference, and a thankful parent who has mini melt-downs every time they are backordered! So in summary: these aren't flaws, it's just the name of the natural binky game!
